    "body": "### Problem\n\nFor more details see https://github.com/neovide/neovide/issues/1641. But, in short, the popup menus are not repositioned to fit inside the screen,\r\n\r\nBy investigating the code, I'm pretty sure that the problem lies here , it does nto seem to do the size calculations when using multigrid https://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/996dd36c77321ea91758b5996d152a2f37af99dd/src/nvim/window.c#L986-L1018\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. Start Neovide with `--multigrid`\r\n2. Open any file which has language support protocol enabled with support for hovering documentation.\r\n3. Either make window small enough (for example splitting) or make sure you have big enough hover documentation available.\r\n4. Open hover e.g. hovering a function / method / struct / class etc. declaration.\r\n5. See if the hover window stays withing the window (and within split window).\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nThe hover should stay within the window boundaries and not overflow to the right.\n\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\n\nNeovim Version 0.8.0 ->\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nN/A\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nAny\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nAny\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nAny\n\n### Installation\n\nAny",
